                   "message":  "SAVEAS-STATUS-SNAPSHOT: forward-only snapshot — Save-As to a new .rge-project tree landed (#283/#284)\n\nRecords that the carried Save-As feature shipped (substrate #283 + wiring #284),\nsuperseding the \"Save-As to a new .rge-project tree remains carried/deferred\"\nline in the 2026-06-01 STATUS-DOC-OPENSAVE-RECONCILE snapshot. Forward-only\nprepend (the #282 4-doc pattern), docs-only, 0 Cargo.toml.\n\n- plans/BASELINE.md: new \"### 2026-06-01 - Save-As to a NEW .rge-project tree\n  landed (#283 substrate + #284 wiring)\" subsection above the byte-identical\n  \"### 2026-06-01 - Editor Open/Save surface landed (#264-#281)\" subsection.\n- Status.md + HANDOFF.md: parallel \"Snapshot: 2026-06-01\" blockquote above the\n  STATUS-DOC-OPENSAVE-RECONCILE snapshot.\n- change.md: a 2026-06-01 entry before the pinned REPO TRANSFER line.\n\nAnti-over-claim: records only that Save-As-to-a-new-tree shipped (Ctrl+Shift+S\n-\u003e SaveSource::Project via save_world_as_new_project). Menu-entry wiring,\nlast-dir-memory dialog, non-empty-folder confirmation, and the non-Open/Save\naudit gaps (drag-drop / io-image / World-only CommandBus context) stay\nexplicitly open. Prior dated entries + the 2026-05-11 one-page summaries are\nbyte-identical (pure prepend).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
